node.text: This Plum Galette from Chef Jacques Pépin is a rustic tart with an elegant finish. The buttery, flaky pâte brisée dough gets filled with fresh, seasonal fruit and baked until richly browned in the oven. A final brushing of fruit preserves provides flavorful and beautiful sheen. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: The inspiration for this Spicy Tofu and Zucchini Stew that @annie.h.shi makes for cozy weeknight dinners every season of the year comes from Soondubu Jjigae, a spicy Korean tofu stew, that she grew up eating at restaurants. The recipe features an umami-rich broth powered by dashi packets, gochugaru, doenjang (fermented soybean paste), and gochujang. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: “I think this cookie is so elegant and so New York chic and I’m gonna take it to SoHo,” says Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) as she adds gold leaf to her take on the classic Black and White cookie. Bling aside, these Black and Ruby Cookies are already extra special with ruby chocolate instead of white, buttermilk instead of whole, and rye flour as a nod to iconic NYC deli breads. Find out how to make them by visiting this link:https://bit.ly/3zD88fk or tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.title: Pastries with Paola | Black and Ruby Cookies

node.text: On this week's episode of Mad Genius, F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple shares corny jokes and his recipe for Whipped Corn Dip with Chile Oil. Tap the link in bio for this a-maize-ing recipe!

node.text: This Plum Galette from Chef Jacques Pépin is a rustic tart with an elegant finish. The buttery, flaky pâte brisée dough gets filled with fresh, seasonal fruit and baked until richly browned in the oven. A final brushing of fruit preserves provides flavorful and beautiful sheen. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: When tomatoes are at their best, take a cue from Hetal Vasavada and don't cook them at all, instead use them to make Kachumber Gazpacho. For this recipe, kachumber, a fresh, cucumber-based Indian salad, is both blended into the soup and sprinkled over the top, adding a fresh crunch and a warm, spicy layer to classic tomato gazpacho. 🍅: @milkandcardamom 📸: @protazio

There's no need to fire up the grill for @laraleefood's spicy, sweet and tangy Balinese Sticky Glazed Pork Ribs. Glazed in a marinade of sticky kecap manis (fermented sweet soy sauce), chilies, garlic, ginger and palm sugar, they’re roasted low and slow in the oven until the meat is fall-off-the-bone tender. Tap the link in bio to watch the full Chefs At Home episode on YouTube!

node.text:
This Roasted Curry Tomato Pie recipe is one that F&W editors have been making all summer long. Turmeric gives the rustic crust a glorious golden glow, but the real stars are the ripe summer tomatoes and tangy tamarind onions, which complement the spiced, cheesy filling beautifully. Tap the link in bio to start baking! 
📸: @gregdupree

node.text: For the final episode of this season of Pastries with Paola, Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) went all out with her own "chic" spin on the iconic New York City treat of her youth: the Black and White cookie. Made with ruby chocolate instead of white, buttermilk instead of whole, rye flour as a nod to iconic NYC deli breads, and gold leaf for an extra special touch, these Black and Ruby Cookies are the next-level dessert you've been looking for. Tap the link in bio for the recipe. #PastrieswithPaola 📸: @reallyfarrah
